===Etymology===
From Anglo-Saxon ''[[hus]]'', '''house''' + ''band'', related to English '''[[band]]''' and '''[[bond]]'''. Alternatively from Scandinavian ''[[husbonde]]'' (house farmer) which was a farmer allowed to work on a piece of the Lords larger estate in feudal times. Being married to such a husbonde would make him your husbonde.

